description:
Read Dave Liebman's essay. Link: https://bit.ly/2xJhNDe

Producers Notes: "Dave Liebman was one of the first musicians to openly state music students should pick a second major for their economic security. Our conversation explores the challenges creative music faces today; from venues, employment, Edu gigs, and more. While the picture Mr. Liebman paints is dark, he reaffirms that we remember the benefits of learning the craft of music. We hope this frank interview will spur conversation and reflection on ways to support creative music, and re-establish the reason we choose to play music,  a life-long passion." -Jonathan Bewley, Snapshots Foundation Director/Producer visit: http://snapshotsfoundation.com/
